The paper deals with rewritability of queries and programs in the context of databases and knowledge representation, which are central topics in the database (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO) sub-categories. The use of expressive description logics and ontology-mediated queries also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The complexity analysis and algorithmic results may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
